 {"id":"franken_networkx-1u5","title":"Expand conformance fixture corpus for matching and centrality variants","description":"Expand fixture corpus to larger legacy families for matching and additional centrality variants. Add oracle-generated fixtures for max_weight_matching, betweenness_centrality, eigenvector_centrality, and katz_centrality against NetworkX reference.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T06:11:47.232131985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T13:43:36.306967392Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T13:43:36.306276695Z","close_reason":"Completed: Added 9 new oracle-anchored conformance fixtures (betweenness_petersen, eigenvector_wheel, katz_barbell, max_weight_large, pagerank_barabasi, closeness_turan, min_weight_bipartite, harmonic_grid, degree_petersen). Also fixed pre-existing flow_min_cut partition mismatch and clippy manual_div_ceil lint in fnx-durability.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-1u7","title":"PERF: onion_layers is 70x slower than NetworkX","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:55:14.056413723Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-02T21:01:52.571836318Z","closed_at":"2026-04-02T21:01:52.571584762Z","close_reason":"Replaced O(V*E) per-layer degree recomputation with incremental degree tracking using adjacency index arrays. Performance improved from 0.14s to 0.007s (20x speedup). Correctness verified against NetworkX.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-1uoos","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] shortest_path(G) arg-less returns dict instead of generator","description":"networkx's shortest_path(G, source=None, target=None) delegates to all_pairs_shortest_path/dijkstra/bellman-ford and returns a generator yielding (source, paths_dict) pairs. fnx.shortest_path(G) in the same no-args case returns a nested dict-of-dicts from the Rust _raw_shortest_path. This breaks callers that iterate the result, call next() on it, or pass it to APIs that expect a generator. shortest_path_length(G) is correct (returns a generator). Fix: wrap the Python shortest_path so that when source is None and target is None, the dict-of-dicts result is materialized into a generator of (src, paths_dict) pairs, matching nx.all_pairs_shortest_path contract.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:10:55.257362331Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:13:26.072774320Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-1xkp","title":"parity: DiGraph pred should satisfy mapping protocol","description":"DiGraph.pred currently fails NetworkX's ordinary mapping protocol. In FrankenNetworkX, pred.get(node, default) is missing entirely and dict(G.pred) raises ValueError instead of producing the upstream {node: AtlasView(...)} predecessor mapping. Match the upstream DiGraph pred mapping contract, including get() and dict(...) conversion.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:46:32.469689487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:04:47.486786968Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T04:04:47.484913933Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-1xwy","title":"Readwrite: preserve # in edgelist attrs with inline comments","description":"Ensure read_edgelist/read_adjlist strip inline comments while escaping # in attributes for round-trip safety.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-11T12:52:36.326145110Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-11T12:54:02.146386915Z","closed_at":"2026-04-11T12:54:02.146132325Z","close_reason":"Completed: escaped # in attrs + added round-trip coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-201f","title":"parity: DiGraph and MultiDiGraph succ should return read-only adjacency views","description":"DiGraph.succ and MultiDiGraph.succ currently expose raw mutable neighbor dicts instead of NetworkX's read-only AtlasView/AdjacencyView wrappers. In FrankenNetworkX, assigning G.succ['a']['x'] = {} is silently accepted and leaves the graph unchanged, while upstream NetworkX raises TypeError. Match the upstream successor-mapping contract on directed graph families.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:42:30.201281327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T07:47:03.912875Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T07:47:03.912875Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
